find ./ -name "file_name"
locate filename
=================================
Regular expression

ls -l abc*
or *abc
?bcd
*bcd*
touch abc{1..9}.txt
=================================
Hard link and soft link

ln orginalfilename linkfilename
ln -s originalfilename linkfilename

==================================
File directory permission

chmod U+w
chown username filename or directory
chgrp groupname filename or directory
=================================
Access control list

To provide special and flexible permission for file systems

setfacl and getfacl
For user:
setfacl -m u:vijayendranramamoorthy:rwx /path

For group:

setfacl -m g:groupname:wx /paths 

To allow all files or dir'sto inherit

setfacl -rm "entry" /path

To remove a specific entry
setfacl -x u:user /path to file

To remove all entries
setfacl -b /path

